Bank Pekao, Mol Shares May Move: Central Europe Stock Preview

-- B y   M a r t a   W a l d o c h   a n d   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-03-09T07:19:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/bank-pekao-mol-shares-may-move-central-europe-stock-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.    Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 0.2 percent, the Czech PX Index
declined 0.3 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index sank 1.3 percent.    Bank Pekao SA (PEO)  : Poland’s second-largest bank said
fourth-quarter profit rose to 643.7 million zloty ($225 million)
from 611.8 million zloty a year earlier, missing the 705.1
million-zloty average estimate of 10 analysts in a Bloomberg
survey.  The bank proposed to pay 6.8 zloty a share as a dividend
from 2010 net profit, up from 2.9 zloty a share a year earlier.
Pekao shares climbed 1.8 percent to 173 zloty.  Mol Nyrt. (MOL HB): Laszlo Varro, vice president for
strategic development at Hungary’s largest oil refiner, will
quit effective March 14, the company said in a statement on its
website. Mol fell 2.5 percent to 23,695 forint.  To contact the reporters on this story:
